    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><note>Il <rs key="#Princeps">principe</rs>
                            <persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/303">Arechi II</persName> offre
                            al monastero di S. Sofia di <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/110"
                                >Benevento</placeName> (prosegue l'elenco iniziato con il doc.
                            3535):</note></ab> <ab>(…) [45] Nec non et <rs key="#Houses">casas</rs> infra <placeName ref="#places/110"
                            key="#Cities #Houses">Beneventanam civitatem</placeName> seu et <rs
                            key="#Casalia">casales</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Villages/settlements #Casalia" ref="#places/3430">ad
                            Pini</placeName> et ad <placeName key="#Villages/settlements #Casalia"
                            ref="#places/3429">Laiano</placeName> quam <name ref="Grauso"
                            >Grauso</name>
                        <rs key="#Writer">notarius</rs> per suam <rs
                            key="#Cartula #Offersio/donatio">offertionis cartulam</rs> in integrum
                        et cum duobus <rs key="#Slave">servis</rs>, <name ref="Pitulus"
                            >Pitulo</name> et <name ref="Maurus">Mauro</name>, cum uxoribus et
                        filiis suis et peculiis, <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/85"
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Casalini/fundamenta #Monasteries #Slave"
                            >Sancte Sophie monasterio</orgName> optulit, nostra vero potestas
                        secundum textum offertionis in predicto <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterio</rs> Sancte Sophie firmabimus possidendum. (…)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p><emph>Editions</emph>: IS1 VIII, col. 578D-579A; IS2 VIII, coll. 31A; IS2 X-2,
                    col. 426D-427A; Borgia 1769, I, p. 293; Cappelletti 1845, p. 41; CSS, I, 1 [45],
                    p. 321 (source of the text reproduced here). <emph>Document summaries</emph>: Di
                    Meo 1795-1819, III, p. 96; Bertolini O, 1926, 72; RIM, 444 (v. 388).</p>
            </div>
